{{Infobox NRHP | name = Lorillard Snuff Mill | nrhp_type = nhl | image = File:Lorillard Snuff Mill in New York Botanical Garden.jpg | caption = Lorillard Snuff Mill in 2011 | location= Snuff Mill Road, [[New York Botanical Gardens]], [[Bronx, New York]] | coordinates = {{coord|40.859681|-73.876174|region:US-NY_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = New York City#New York#USA | built = {{start date|1840}} | architect = P. Lorillard Co. | architecture = | designated_nrhp_type= December 22, 1977<ref name="nhlsum">{{cite web|url=http://tps.cr.nps.gov/nhl/detail.cfm?ResourceId=1727&ResourceType=Building|title=Lorillard Snuff Mill|date=2007-09-15|work=National Historic Landmark summary listing|publisher=National Park Service|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605232030/http://tps.cr.nps.gov/nhl/detail.cfm?ResourceId=1727&ResourceType=Building|archivedate=2011-06-05|df=}}</ref> | added = December 22, 1977<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2007a}}</ref> | area = {{convert|5|acre|ha}} | governing_body = Local | refnum = 77000935<ref name="nris"/> | designated_other2_name = NYC Landmark | designated_other2_date = April 19, 1966 | designated_other2_abbr = NYCL | designated_other2_link = New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission | designated_other2_number = | designated_other2_color = #ff0000 |nrhp_type2 = cp |designated_nrhp_type2 = May 28, 1967 |partof = [[New York Botanical Garden]] |partof_refnum = 67000009 }}
The '''Lorillard Snuff Mill''' now known as the '''Lillian and Amy Goldman Stone Mill''', is the oldest existing [[tobacco]] manufacturing building in the United States. It was built around 1840 next to the [[Bronx River]] to supplement an earlier building of the same function. The [[schist]] that makes up its walls was quarried locally. It was declared a [[National Historic Landmark]] in 1977 and is located inside the [[New York Botanical Garden]], itself an NHL.<ref name="nhlsum"/><ref name="nrhpinv">{{Cite journal|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory-Nomination: Lorillard Snuff Mill|url={{NHLS url|id=77000935}} |format=pdf|author=George R. Adams|date=December 1976|publisher=National Park Service}} and {{NHLS url|id=77000935|title=Accompanying photos, exterior, from 1976 and c.1902.|photos=y}}&nbsp;{{small|(1.90&nbsp;MB)}}</ref>
[[File:Lorillard Snuff Mill (EXTERIOR VIEW).jpg|thumb|left|Snuff mill in 1936]] The [[Lorillard Tobacco Company|Lorillard]] firm was founded by [[Pierre Abraham Lorillard]] in 1760. His two sons, Peter and George, took over after he was killed during the [[American Revolutionary War]], and they moved the manufacturing portion of the business to this location in the Bronx in 1792.<ref name="nrhpinv"/> Peter Lorillard III built a forty-five room mansion, stone cottage and stables nearby. The mansion burned in 1923. The Lorillard company and family left the property in the Bronx in 1870 after relocating their business to Jersey City, NJ. The land was purchased by New York city in 1884 and was transferred to the [[New York Botanical Gardens]] in 1915. The Mill was retained by New York City Department of Parks and used for storage and shops until 1937 when it too was transferred to the Botanical Garden along with several other small parcels. The Mill was renovated in 1952-54 and a cafe and patio were installed on the lower side facing the Bronx River, and a meeting room was fashioned from the space that once held snuff-grinding equipment. The building had a $10.5 million restoration in 2010 and is now used for staff offices and a catering facility.<ref name="Kirsch">{{cite web|last=Kirsch|first=Abigail|title=The Snuff Mill Gallery|url=http://www.abigailkirsch.com/exclusive-locations/the-new-york-botanical-garden-stone-mill/|publisher=Abigail Kirsch|accessdate=7 August 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110517052048/http://www.abigailkirsch.com/exclusive-locations/the-new-york-botanical-garden-stone-mill/|archivedate=17 May 2011|df=}}</ref><ref name=nyt2009>{{cite web|last=Dunlap|first=David W.|title=From Tobacco Leaves to Wedding Bouquets, 169 Years in the Bronx|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/02/09/nyregion/09snuff.html|work=February 8, 2009|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=7 April 2012}}</ref>
