{{italic title}}
'''''The Dante Encyclopedia''''', edited by Richard Lansing,<ref>{{cite book|last1=Alighieri|first1=Dante|last2=Lombardo|first2=Stanley|title=Inferno|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SXX9pMFCR8IC&pg=PR43|accessdate=11 April 2012|year=2009|publisher=Hackett|isbn=9780872209176|page=43}}</ref> is a reference book for the life and works of [[Dante Alighieri|Dante]], especially the ''[[Divine Comedy]]''.<ref name="Kirkpatrick2004">{{cite book|last=Kirkpatrick|first=Robin|title=Dante, The Divine Comedy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iM0OBp1zGYYC&pg=PA117|accessdate=11 April 2012|year=2004|publisher=Cambridge UP|isbn=9780521539944|page=117}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Eberhart|first=George M.|year=2000|title=Rev. of Lansing, ''Dante Encyclopedia''|journal=[[College & Research Libraries News]]|volume=61|issue=10|pages=945–48|issn=0099-0086}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|year=2003|title=Rev. of Lansing, ''Dante Encyclopedia''|journal=[[Forum for Modern Language Studies]]|volume=39|issue=1|pages=97–98|issn=0015-8518|doi=10.1093/fmls/39.1.97-c}}</ref> Originally published in hardback in 2000, the book appeared in paperback in 2010.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Magnabosco|first=Francesca|year=2011|title=Rev. of Lansing, ''Dante Encyclopedia''|journal=[[Modern Language Review]]|volume=106|issue=2|pages=563–64|jstor=10.5699/modelangrevi.106.2.0563}}</ref>

==Reviews==
The ''Dante Encyclopedia'' was published to positive reviews. ''[[Library Journal]]'' recommended the book highly, calling it "an indispensable reference work for most libraries, ... an excellent point of entry" for any student of Dante.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Christian|first=Graham|year=2000|title=Rev. of Lansing, ''Dante Encyclopedia''|journal=[[Library Journal]]|volume=125|issue=13|pages=84–86}}</ref>

